HEADWORD: Disworship
<hw>Dis*wor"ship</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To refuse to
worship; to treat as unworthy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

